Supplier Proposal Workflow

Construction projects involve multiple suppliers.

Examples:

electricians

plumbers

facade installers

insulation contractors

roofing specialists

Each project defines multiple work items.

Examples of work items:

facade installation

structural concrete

electrical wiring

plumbing

roofing

Suppliers submit proposals for work items.

Proposal contents

A supplier proposal usually contains:

supplier name

work item reference

estimated cost

execution timeline

technical notes

Proposal approval

Project managers review submitted proposals and approve one.

Once approved:

The proposal becomes the active supplier assignment.

Rejected proposals remain stored for reference.

Pricing rules

Prices can change while a proposal is under review.

After approval, the price is normally fixed.

However, changes may still occur through addendums.

Addendums represent additional work that was not originally planned.
